This paper deals with multi-agent reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper specifically focuses on a linear quadratic regulator problem, which is a control theory problem and falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). The use of actor-critic algorithms suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with multiple agents, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the paper's focus on hierarchical algorithms suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of robotics (cs.RO).
